<s> node.insertAfter(newKid,refChild), if it existed, would be precisely equivalent to node.insertBefore(newKid,refChild.getNextSibling()).  </s>
<s> Note that inserting before null means inserting at the end of the list, so the Right Thing should happen even in that case.  </s>
<s> Also note that a shorthand in that case is node.appendChild(newKid).  </s>
<s> So insertAfter might be convenient, but isn't strictly necessary.  </s>
<s> Which is why we left it out of Level 1. Joe Kesselman / IBM Research  </s>
